A stab in the dark: Are you using JUnit 4.x or 3.X? It seems that you are
using the 3.x jars and there Test is not an annotation, it&#39;s a regular
interface.
If you switch to JUnit 4.x you also need to remove &quot;extends TestCase&quot;
(otherwise JUnit4 will try to be backwards compatible and look for methods
starting with &quot;test&quot; rather than methods annotated with @test).

I hope this brings you closer to the solution.
